<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="906" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2145a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-30T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1915, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2652. <persName corresp="#p_ACP1">Chandler Anderson</persName>,
                                representing some of the beef packers, sailed steamer <hi rend="italic">Rotterdam</hi> December 28 to treat for settlement
                                direct with British Government. Kindly give him such unofficial
                                assistance as you properly can.</p>
                            <p>British Ambassador here thought that any note on beef packers’ cases
                                should be withheld pending negotiations of settlement as it might
                                make settlement impossible.</p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Lloyd</persName> Griscom sailed same
                                ship, representing Sulzberger, to try to open negotiations for
                                settlement. British Government has copies of agreements between
                                Sulzberger and Deutsche Bank which insured. Sulzberger against loss
                                in case of seizure. Griscom knows Government has this
                                information.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>